The paper deals with visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning-based methods for visual tracking, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
